				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">AE kiting after Dulaks (55-65!)<a name="55595"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Aug 7 04 9:58 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>For all those trying to AE kite past 55ish and are finding that the light bues in dulaks are just getting too crowded, I have found a sweet AE spot ;The Luggald Abomination room in Nadox.
<br />

<br />
The main room past the lava bridge has 4 little rooms, one at each corner. If you are carefull you can pull all 4 rooms and the main room all in one kite. I usualy hit my 2:30 seols before i zone in, then cast invis and make a break for the lugs. Once you have all the little rooms and the main room pulled just go to the center of the main room and circle between the 4 pillars. Obviously this is an indoor dungeon so you cannot autocircle due to lack of seols, but with run 3 i find it very easy to stay safely away from the group yet still be hitting them with my AE songs.
<br />

<br />
loot here is pretty decent, the lugs drop Brined armbands which i sell in baazar for 1.5k (if they werent lore i'd be rich), gems and such, And i have never seen anyone anywhere near that set of rooms. They have alot of hp so it takes a little longer to do than Dulaks, but at 55 i was etting 30% of a level each time i kited the place, or well over a full AA.
<br />

<br />
hope this heps, and/or negates the flames im gonna get for my post on Dulak ae kiting
<br />

<br />
Christione De'Lukka - 57 Bard (The Nameless)
<br />
</span></td>
