				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: AE kiting after Dulaks (55-65!)<a name="56266"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Aug 11 04 9:44 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>I have an update for you all, as I was going from my kite spot at upper lugs to hates fury i noticed a large abundace of the undead trolls along the way. I also noticed the nice big square docks right before teh HF zone in, (you know where this is going). Well the xp from that kite was comperable to the luggald kite, but the loot was about 10 tiems better as the trolls drop vendor stuffs more often. I just followed the southern exit from upper luggalds (see above map), grabbed the bg room tehn headed to the 2nd dock platform right before the Hates Fury zone. this is kinda tricky with only run3 so i advise getin a sow before you zone into nadox then once you have your kite going click it off and stick with run3.
<br />

<br />
The dock is just big enough to kite on so you want to be very carefull wen kiting there, the realy big difference here is that you can zone if you feel you are falling asleep midkite =)
<br />
Oh and the undead resist a lot less too.
<br />

<br />
hope that helps ya 
<br />
Christione - The Nameless 
<br />

<br />
OK little update:
<br />

<br />
I tried doin this area again, this time starting on the dock, rounding them up ten running out and getting the rest. This seems to be mch easier and safer because the dock round up is hard to do without being stunned. Better to get stunned by 6-7 trolls than 50 of em. that way you dont get flattened like an enchanter without RuneIII.</span></td>
