				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: AE kiting after Dulaks (55-65!)<a name="57094"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Aug 17 04 10:58 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>You can do the upper luggald room in one kite, then do the lower room (incubator room) in one kite.  If you have the aa, and a decent instrument, you can clear both rooms and then wait a couple minutes for repop of the first room.  This is a straight up AE kite. 
<br />

<br />
You can easily do this with run3, though I happen to have run 4 atm.  :p
<br />

<br />
For the upper room, I tag the 2 wanderers, then go to the corner room to the left of the passage that leads to the lava bridge.  Circle that room to aggro everything, then go to each corner room in turn counter-clockwise (room to the right of the lava passage, room in the far right corner, then room in the far left corner).  I found that this minimized the chances of getting stunned and killed.  The first couple rooms you'll take some hits, and the fewer luggalds you have the better chance you'll survive.  Once you've got the 4 corner rooms, you'll have pulled most everything, and you may have to circle the main room a couple times to get any that you didn't catch as you were headed for the corner rooms.  There's also a wandering undead troll you can sometimes pickup too, but that's not a problem.  Once you get the pattern down, you rarely get hit.  Kite in the center of the main room.  
<br />

<br />
Have an abomination (or Kraska if the named is up) targeted so you know how long your kite is going to last.  The critters will die in 2 stages, Initiates, then abominations.  The initiates will die when the abominations are at about 15% health (the 1 troll in the room, and the undead troll will die when the abominations are at about 25-30%).  Do this room first, so you can get the potential deathspawn Garodizan Razorfin out of the way (there's a reason for this).  He can spawn from the death of any luggald. 
<br />

<br />
For the lower room, start in the passage from the lava bridge, tag the abomination that wanders the hall, and then invis and cross to the other side of the room to the hallway that leads to the room with the apprentices.  Do not aggro the apprentices, they are casters and will mess you up.  This hall is wide enough that if you hang out in one (far) corner (I usually use the right corner closest to the apprentice room), all the stuff that has aggroed from the abomination following you will be on one side, and you can leave the hall along the other wall and not get hit.  Once back in the main chamber, circle a little to get the stuff you have closer, then pull the left side room up the steps.  Once you have that stuff, and are in the main room, pull the rest of the main room, then circle a little to get everything packed up and pull the right side room up the steps.  You'll do the kite in that small room.  This way you get everything that's important (you may miss 1 incubator if he's wandered next to the apprentices), but what's important are the luggald chosen.  
<br />

<br />
The critters in this room die in three stages (I don't count the abomination) and are higher level than the upper room, so it'll take a bit longer.   First the incubators, then the chosen, then the guardians and overseer.  Have the overseer targeted (or the named that can spawn in his place) for estimation on the kite time.  Incubators will die when the guardians are at about 25%, the chosen when they are about 15%, and then the guardians will die (the overseer will be one of the last things to die).  
<br />

<br />
The reason you want to do the abomination room first is to maximize the chance that Garodizan won't be the deathspawn for the chosen (since he can spawn from any luggald death) The chosen have their own deathspawn, Tarsos (something).  He can drop a charm that you can sell, or a hybrid belt with FT1.  The belt sells really well.  
<br />

<br />
This is what I usually do when I'm getting aa and PL'ing an alt.  I still manage to die 1-3 times a session though, usually from a lag spike.  More often when I had fewer aa, way less often now that I have better stuff and more aa.  
<br />

<br />
The exp is comparable to PoF (at least pof field 2, tables seems perma-camped so I haven't ever tried there) if you can clear both rooms.  I get about 70% of an aa every 45 mins.  I usually make about 1500pp an hour in gem loot, with the chance for sellable stuff from the named.  I have trouble selling the brined armbands or the coral studded collar for more than 15pp on povar, so I never bother with them.  There's also a slim chance for a coral dagger from the bottom room as a random drop from the chosen or the overseer, and that sells pretty well too.  
<br />

<br />
If you are PL'ing a friend (or an alt), then the kite spots I suggest are great.  Even if invis wears off, they will have time to re-invis before anything paths back to them.  For the upper room, park the toon in the passage from lava on the rock.  For the lower room, the toon can hang out on the rock in the corner of the passage from the lava.  
<br />

<br />
I rarely if ever see anyone camping the luggalds on Povar, but I can't say how it is on other servers.  </span></td>
			</tr><tr>
